#   usage at lines 16-25 (the const usage block)
#   parse_argv at lines 37-39 (2 flag.BoolVar calls)
#   actions at lines 41-54 (install-system-units +
#     install-sshd-config + default list-hostkeys flow)
#   default socket at line 56 (hardcoded
#     `/var/tmp/ssh-tpm-agent.sock`)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# ssh-tpm-hostkeys is the **host-key lister + bootstrap
# helper** of the ssh-tpm-* family.  Without flags, it
# connects to the ssh-tpm-agent socket at
# `/var/tmp/ssh-tpm-agent.sock` and lists all loaded host
# keys (similar to `ssh-add -L` for the regular ssh-agent).
# With `--install-system-units`, it copies the systemd
# .socket + .service units to `/etc/systemd/system/` for
# system-wide host-key-agent usage.  With `--install-sshd-
# config`, it drops a sshd config snippet pointing at the
# agent socket.
#
# Critical extraction note: ssh-tpm-hostkeys has the
# SMALLEST flag surface of the ssh-tpm-* family — only 2
# flags total, BOTH boolean.  No positional arguments.  The
# completion's 3 documented invocation patterns at usage
# lines 17-18 are:
#   `ssh-tpm-hostkeys`                           (list keys)
#   `ssh-tpm-hostkeys --install-system-units`    (install
#                                                 systemd units)
#   `ssh-tpm-hostkeys --install-sshd-config`     (install
#                                                 sshd snippet)
#
# Critical extraction note: both install flags trigger
# early-exit at main.go:47 and main.go:53 — they do NOT
# combine with the list-keys flow.  Order of precedence:
# `--install-system-units` (line 41) wins if BOTH install
# flags are passed (the second `if` block runs unreachable
# code after os.Exit(0)).

_arguments \
  '-install-system-units[install systemd .socket + .service units to /etc/systemd/system/ for system-wide use]' \
  '-install-sshd-config[install sshd config snippet pointing at the ssh-tpm-agent socket]'
